Simple Open Document Spreadsheet py

Simple pure python spreadsheet class with Open Document Spreadsheet support.

	* Pure python implementation
	* Set cell value and style using it's spreadsheet name (e.g. "A3" or "B4:C5")
	* Set and calculate simple formulas (e.g. "A3*2+B5" or "SUM(B4:C5)")
	* Set conditional styles (e.g. "cell-content()<=0")
	* Import and export xml files
	* Export html and csv files
	* Export Excel xls files (requires xlwt-future installed)
	* Import and export Open Document Format ods files (requires odfpy installed, but odfpy doesn't support Python 3)
	* Export Excel xlsx files (requires openpyxl installed, but with some errors)

Install
	* python setup.py install
	
